    public interface UsesCustomNull
    Interface implemented by some enums and mostly other Immutable structs that have custom "null" behavior in place of Java's built-in null.

    NOTE: There is also an informal "statically polymorphic" contract imposed by this interface that says an implementor must have a public static final NULL member or method. For enums this simply means having a NULL entry.

    NOTE ALSO: Another soft contract imposed by this interface is that the library (in this case SweetBlue) hosting the implementor must never return an actually null reference of the implementor.
